# Project Map is required reading

Before responding to ANY task in this repo, **read `PROJECT-MAP.md`** at the
repo root. It documents the stack, the Supabase schema/quirks, the server-fn +
TanStack Query data-flow, conventions, and the file map — treat it as ground
truth so you don't re-explore the whole project.

## Read first

- Read `PROJECT-MAP.md` at the start of every task (even small ones) before
  planning or editing.
- Follow its conventions (Bun via `bun --bun`, `#/*` alias, server-only
  Supabase client, server functions + `*QueryOptions`, shadcn install command,
  URL search-param state, promotion abbreviations mapped in code).
- Do not hand-edit `src/routeTree.gen.ts` (generated).

## Update after changes

`PROJECT-MAP.md` MUST stay accurate. In the **same task** that you make a
change, update the matching section (see its §11 "Maintaining this file"):

- Routes / server functions / `src/lib` modules → update the file map & feature notes
- Schema, migrations, RLS, indexes → update the Supabase + data-model sections
- Dependencies, scripts, tooling, env vars → update the stack/running/env sections
- New data quirks or gotchas → add a short note

If a change makes any part of `PROJECT-MAP.md` wrong or incomplete, fix it
before finishing. Keep edits concise and factual.
